author: The Capital-Journal
title: Local sports briefs for Oct. 13: ESU softball coach to accept job in Florida
text:
Local sports briefs for Oct. 13: ESU softball coach to accept job in Florida Posted: October 13, 2015 - 10:51pm By The Capital-Journal 
Emporia State softball coach Julie LeMaire will step down as the Hornets’ coach after accepting the coaching position at Nova Southeastern University in Fort Lauderdale, Fla., ESU announced Tuesday. 
LeMaire, who coached at ESU for four seasons, will leave the university ranked second in winning percentage and third in total wins. LeMaire was a two-time MIAA coach of the year and posted a 164-65 record during her tenure at Emporia State. 
K-STATE’S BECKLER FINISHES TOP 5 IN COLLEGE GOLF DEBUT: Kansas State freshman Andrew Beckler, a former Washburn Rural standout, shot 2-under 70 on Tuesday at Overland Park’s Milburn Golf & Country Club to tie for fourth place in his collegiate debut. 
Beckler, who shot another 2-under 70 during the second round, made five birdies on the day and finished the tourney at even-par 216. He was the top finisher for the Wildcats.
